text:
I legitimately consider the Portal games among the very best games ever. I have never once come across a person who dislikes them.

They are very well made - simple mechanics allowing for extreme complexity, teaching you slowly how to use it all as they go on until you can run through the final levels that combine all of it fluently. A simple yet engaging setting connecting it all together using interesting characters.
Even in the tiny details you can see how well crafted it all is: For example, there is no way to get stuck in this game ever (except for maybe the rare source engine glitch). In the worst case you catapulted yourself into a corner you're not supposed to be in and can drop into the void/goo to respawn. You can not accidentally lock yourself in a spot or destroy something you need without a way to recover. You can never truly fail, while still working hard enough to make success worth celebrating.
